{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/punc/punc-04213/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PUNC-04213"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:42:13"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Punch-Drunk Love"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tracking"]}},{"label":{"none":["Lighting"]},"value":{"none":["high key"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["three shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman sits in a chair with downcast eyes."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-04213/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PUNC-04213","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-04213/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PUNC-04213"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-04213/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-04213/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-04213/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-04213/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-04213/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-04213/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-04213/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-04213/canvas/1/a5e5af6f-92dc-4165-9684-2c8e168bed4e","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2025-08-20T20:58:34.672Z","creator":"Olivia Flores","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>This scene, in which we're introduced to Georgia while a mother holds a baby in the background, alludes to one of PTA's favorite directors. In Robert Altman's <em>Short Cuts</em> (1993), Jennifer Jason Leigh's Lois is a phone sex line worker who holds her baby while taking calls.</p>"}],"target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-04213/canvas/1#xywh=146,147,397,663"},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-04213/canvas/1/0b6054ff-4344-4d43-b703-3e8e58a9881e","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2025-08-20T20:59:05.616Z","creator":"Olivia Flores","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Georgia also wears red (and blue jeans) in an inversion of Lena’s role in Barry’s life. Despite her status as one of the \"enemies\" of the film, her expression here makes it clear that she is lonely and sad, just like Barry and Lena.</p>"}],"target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-04213/canvas/1#xywh=551,144,886,798"}]}]}]}